-- Ex-Hevesi Adviser Got $19 Million Pushing $5 Billion in Deals, Cuomo Says
-- Karen Freifeld
-- 2010-06-14T17:14:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/ex-hevesi-adviser-got-19-million-pushing-5-billion-in-deals-cuomo-says.html

          
          
             The indicted former chief political
adviser to ex-New York state Comptroller Alan Hevesi pushed $5
billion in New York state pension fund transactions to enrich
himself with $19 million in fees, according to New York Attorney
General Andrew Cuomo.  
